        TRANSMISSION CONTROL PROTOCOL(TCP)
            WHAT IS TCP?
                - TCP is sort of like the post man of the internet, it ensures that the data sent from one device reaches another accurately and in the correct format and order. 
                - its a protocols meaning its a set of rules that devices follow to communicate with each other.
            WHAT ARE THE KEY CHARACTERISTICS ON TCP
                - Stands for transmission control protocols
                - connection oriented meaning that bbefore any data is sent a connection is essablished between the two devices(sort of like a phone call you must dial and connect before you can speak).
                - Requires a handshake  meaning two devices agree to communicate like when you shake hands with somepne to confirm you are onthe same page (in networking this handshake is a 3 step device to ensure both devices are ready tpo send and recieve data)
                - reliable data tranfer, TCP ensures that all data sent is reciceved correctly on the other end, meaning any data is lost or corrupted is TCP will resend it and thats why its reliable. 
            WHAT ARE THE USE CASES IN TCP?
                - TCP ensures data is delieverd in order.
                - error checking and flow control, TCP checks for errors in the data and controls the flow of data to avoid congestion insuring smooth and error free information transfer.
                - TCP allows for bidirectionsal communication, it can be used whenever two devices need to communicate back and forth for example emails, web browsing amd file transfer.
        USER DATAGRAM PROTOCOL (UDP)
            - UDP is a simple protocol used to send and recicve data unlike TCP UDP is connectionless.
            - WHAT ARE THE KEY CHARACTERISTICS ON UDP
                - stands for User datagram Protocol  
                - its a simple protocol to send and receive data its straight forward and doesnt require much over head making it quick and easy to use.
                - No Prior communication need data can be sent immediatly without waiting to establish communication, but the downside to this is theres no guarantee that the data will reach its destination 
                - Its also connectionless meaning no prior communication needs to be established between sender and receiver as each packet is sent independatly. 
                - Fast but unreliable since theres no onnection set up nor is there error checking UDP is much faster then TCP, but this speed comes at a cost of reliablity.
            WHAT ARE THE COMMON FUNCTIONS FOR UDP
                - UDP is suitable for real time application such as live streaming, online gaming and many other hwere speed is more important then reliablity.
                - DNS 
                - VPN (virtual private network) some VPn networks use UDP because its faster and works better for streaming 
